code_changes.content:
{
  "buggy_files": ["drivers/ata/libata-core.c"],
  "buggy_functions": ["ata_device_blacklist"],
  "confidence": 0.95,
  "reasoning": "The bug is caused by the Samsung SSD 860 EVO not being included in the ata_device_blacklist array in drivers/ata/libata-core.c. This array (defined at line 4393) contains device entries that have the ATA_HORKAGE_NO_NCQ_TRIM flag to disable queued TRIM commands. In kernel 4.14.114, entries exist for 'Samsung SSD 840*' (line 4562) and 'Samsung SSD 850*' (line 4564), but there is no entry for 'Samsung SSD 860*'. The bug report shows SEND FPDMA QUEUED command timeouts during fstrim on the 860 EVO. The fix is to add an entry like { \"Samsung SSD 860*\", NULL, ATA_HORKAGE_NO_NCQ_TRIM | ATA_HORKAGE_ZERO_AFTER_TRIM } to the ata_device_blacklist array, similar to the existing Samsung 840/850 entries. This is confirmed by the modern kernel (github.com/torvalds/linux) which has this exact fix at lines 4271-4274."
}

